<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>9001</id>
	<title>Enhancement: better error message when tag cannot be matched to local repos</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">mentioned in #8975</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Docker does not give a descriptive error if you try to use a local image by name without specifying a correct tag if no latest exists.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">i.e if you create a local image with a specific version `demo/baseimage:0.0.1` and then use it in the dockerfile as</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">```
FROM demo/baseimage
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Then it tries to pull the repo (which obviously won't exist on dockerhub) and then gives this:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">```
Pulling repository demo/centos-baseimage
2014/11/06 08:39:46 Error: image demo/centos-baseimage not found
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">@thaJeztah suggested</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">```
Error: image demo/centos-baseimage:latest not found
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
